          <h3>Person records and the family tree</h3>
          <p>Most often you will interact with the knowledgebase by viewing, editing and creating individual person records. From time to time you may wish to view (parts of) the family tree where you will see the relationships between people through the generations. Familiaris enables you to view the tree in a variety of ways: the tree of all ancestors of a particular person, the male or female line of ancestors of a particular person and the descendants of a particular person.
          </p>
          <p>
          In typical use you will go to the Knowledgebase page to search for a person by specifying their name and birth date, which will display the person record ready for you to study and edit. Once at a specific person page you can choose to view the ancestors of that person. To see other versions of the family tree go to the Family Tree page.
          </p>
          
          <h3 id="examples">Examples</h3>
          <p>
           In this section there are examples of how to use the website for common tasks. It assumes that you have signed in and are viewing the home page. Your first action is to use the main menu across the top of the home page to choose the most appropriate page for the task.
          </p>
          <h5>A. View the information about a particular person</h5>
          <p>
            <ol>
              <li> Go to the Knowledgebase page. </li>
              <li> Use the menu on the left hand column and click on either 'Get my details' to view the information about yourself or click on 'Find person' to search for a specific person.</li>
              <li> If you have clicked on 'Find person' a form will appear into which you can enter the name of the person and their date of birth (needed to distinguish between different people with the same name).</li>
              <li> If the search is successful the details for the person found will appear for you to view. If the search finds multiple people matching your search criteria they will be listed and you can choose one to look at.</li>
            </ol>
          </p>
          <h5>B. Edit the information about a particular person</h5>
          <p>
            <ol>
              <li> Go to the Knowledgebase page. </li>
              <li> Click on 'Find person' to find the record for the required person; follow the instructions in Example A to obtain the required person.</li>
              <li> A person record is displayed on a single page having four main sections:
                <ol>
                  <li>Top-left: an area for displaying a photo of the person with buttons that enable you to add to a gallery of photos and to display all photos. You can choose the photo from the gallery that you wish to be displayed on the person page.
                  <li>Top-right: data that identifies the person including names, data of birth and place of birth. All identification fields can be edited once the 'Enable Editing' button has been pressed. It is possible for an individual to have (or have had) several nicknames and last names, and clicking on a 'More' button will display a list of all known nicknames/last names. You can add to or edit the list. One identification field shows the individuals 'status': alive or dead (there are restrictions on what you can do to alter the details of someone who is alive).
                  <li>Below the photo area: relationship data showing the person's parents, siblings and partner (if any). The names are clickable so that you can move quickly to the pages for these people.
                  </li>
                  <li>The bottom area: a list of categories of information about the person (e.g. their partnership(s), where they have lived, education, medical history and much more). Click on one of the category heading to view the data. It is possible to add new items to each category and to edit the existing items.
                  </li>
                </ol>
              </li>
              <li> If the search is successful the details for the person found will appear for you to examine. If the search finds multiple people matching your search criteria they will be listed and you can choose one to view.</li>
            </ol>
          </p>
          <h5>C. Quickly access a specific person record</h5>
          <p>
          There is a mechanism for helping you to access a particular person's record called 'remembering'. Having accessed a person's page you can click on the memu item 'Remember person' and the system will save a reference to this person. Thereafter, when you want to access a person record the system will present you with a list of your remembered people from which you can choose one to be displayed thereby avoiding having to type in that person's names and date of birth and perform a search.
          </p>
          <p>
          There is a menu item for deleting the currently displayed person from the list of remembered people and one for displaying the list of remembered people. <span><a href="#guide-top">[Back to top]</a></span>
          </p>

